OL,3,C'It's scarred me, just you can't see
OL,4,Cmy scars' - one woman's story of abuse
OL,6,FA woman from the North East says the
OL,7,Fdomestic abuse she suffered has
OL,8,Fscarred her even though she wasn't
OL,9,Fsubjected to physical violence.
OL,11,FClaire, not her real name, is sharing
OL,12,Fher experience on the day the National
OL,13,FPolicing Statement for Violence
OL,14,FAgainst Women and Girls shows nearly
OL,15,F3,000 crimes are recorded every day.
OL,17,FShe told ITV Tyne Tees: "To a certain
OL,18,Fextent I'm thankful that I wasn't
OL,19,Fsubjected to violence but on the other
OL,20,Fhand the mental abuse, it's scarred
OL,21,Fme, just you can't see my scars."
