OL,3,C'It's scarred me, just you can't see
OL,4,Cmy scars' - one woman's story of abuse
OL,6,FClaire hopes speaking about her
OL,7,Fexperience in an abusive relationship
OL,8,Fhelps even one other person spot the
OL,9,Fearly signs and seek help.
OL,11,F"To people outside of the relationship
OL,12,Fthe perpetrator is very charming and
OL,13,Fcomes across as very loveable, the
OL,14,Fperfect partner," she explained.
