OL,3,C'It's scarred me, just you can't see
OL,4,Cmy scars' - one woman's story of abuse
OL,6,F"But being out in a crowd, with
OL,7,Ffriends, with family, being in a
OL,8,Fconversation and holding hands, you
OL,9,Ffeel that squeeze and it makes you
OL,10,Fthink, oh no, I've said something
OL,11,Fwrong I know what's going to happen
OL,12,Fwhen I get home. The barrage of abuse
OL,13,Fwould start."
OL,15,FMore than one million violent crimes
OL,16,Fagainst women and girls were recorded
OL,17,Fby police in 2022/23, according to the
OL,18,Freport by the National Police Chiefs'
OL,19,FCouncil and the College of Policing.
