OL,6,FSuch crimes accounted for nearly 20%
OL,7,Fof all police-recorded crimes
OL,8,Fexcluding fraud in England and Wales
OL,9,Fbetween April 2022 and March 2023.
OL,11,FDeputy Chief Constable Maggie Blyth,
OL,12,Ffrom the College of Policing, said the
OL,13,Ffigures were 'staggering'. Adding, the
OL,14,Fcriminal justice system was 'under-
OL,15,Fperforming for victims', with the
OL,16,Freport stating violence against women
OL,17,Fand girls was at such a scale 'it
OL,18,Fcannot be addressed through law
OL,19,Fenforcement alone'.
